Package gw.api.modules.rest.framework.v1.auth.jwt.matchers

Interface UserTypeMatcher

All Known Implementing Classes:
ClaimMatcher, ContactAuthorizationIdsMatcher, DefaultMatcher, GwabuidMatcher, InternalUserMatcher, PolicyNumbersMatcher, ProducerCodesMatcher, ServiceMatcher
public interface UserTypeMatcher
Interface with methods for working with JWTs and user types, or resource access strategies. There should be at most one implementation of this interface for a given strategy. For a given strategy, the associated matcher will know how to determine whether a JWT or AuthorizedUser is applicable, and how to create an AuthorizedUser out of a JWT.

    • matches

    • getUserType

      String getUserType()
      Returns the type of user that this matcher is associated with; must be unique across all matcher types. That is, every instance of a given matcher type should return the same value, and instances of different types should return different values. This value is used to populate the appropriate AuthorizedUser's attributes, and is linked to a corresponding access.yaml file in apiconfig files.
      Returns:
      type of user being validated

    • createUser

      AuthorizedUser createUser(JsonObject body)
      Creates an AuthorizedUser for this user type. Each invocation of this method should return a new instance.
      Parameters:
      body - JsonObject containing the body of the jwt used to populate the AuthorizedUser's attributes
      Returns:
      AuthorizedUser containing the attributes extracted from the jwt
